# .clinerules — AvihuSitton.com

## Before every change — run these 3 checks internally

### QA Hat
- What could break as a result of this change?
- Does this affect any other pages or components beyond the one requested?
- Are there links, forms, or interactive elements that need manual testing after the change?

### Frontend / UX Hat
- Is the change visually consistent with the rest of the site (colors, fonts, spacing)?
- Does the layout work on both mobile and desktop?
- Is RTL (Hebrew text direction) preserved correctly?

### Content / Brand Hat
- Does any new text match the tone of the site (warm, personal, professional)?
- Is there any placeholder text (e.g. "Lorem ipsum") left behind?

## Iron Rules
- Never delete existing code before understanding its purpose. If unsure — ask.
- Never change more than what was requested. If you spot another issue — report it, do not fix it without approval.
- After every change — briefly state: what was changed, and what should be tested manually.
- If the request is unclear — ask one focused question before starting.
- Before any infrastructure change (deploy, dependencies, API routes, SSR, CSP) — read ARCHITECTURE.md first.

## Red Flags — Stop and ask before doing
- Deleting any file
- Changing navigation structure
- Changing or touching any form (contact form)
- Any change touching SEO (meta tags, H1 headings, URL structure)
- Adding a new external library
- Any change to wrangler.jsonc, next.config.js, or CI/CD workflows
- Any new browser API usage — check SSR compatibility in ARCHITECTURE.md first
